  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Scale-Up of High Impact Intervention for Improved Nutrition in Children and Women in Isiolo and Samburu</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Assessment and profiling of the health facility services and staffing gaps, training of staff in maternity facilities on Baby Friendly Hospital Initiative (BFHI), on-the-job training (OJT) for health workers, on-the-job mentoring of 50 Community Health Workers (CHWs) on identification and referral of malnourished children, formation and regular education sessions for Mother Support Groups (MCGs), and screening of all children under 5 and referral of malnourished children.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support the Ministry of Public Health and Sanitation (MoPHS) and Ministry of Medical Services in Isiolo district to scale-up and deliver high impact nutrition interventions at health facility and community levels, to support District Health Management Team (DHMT) and District Nutrition Officer (DNO) to strengthen their capacity by ensuring that coordination systems are fully operational at the District level, and to ensure quality and timely reporting of key health and nutrition indicators and supplies at the health facility and district levels.</narrative>
  </description>
